*************Installation for linux************************ 

To install kannada tex run shell script insengkan.sh

To uninstall kannada tex run shell script uninsengkan.sh

***********************************************************

*************Installation for windows**********************

To install kannada TeX for windows run instktex.bat batch file.

To uninstall kannada tex run uninktex.bat batchfile.

***********************************************************

*********************USAGE*********************************

include \usepackage{kanlel} to activate kannada as default

manual for kannadatex is manual.pdf and one example file is udaya.tex.


Type1 fonts for kannada TeX/LaTeX are in kantype1 directory which 

also contains readme file. You will need to install these type1 fonts

for better rendering of PDF files. 
